html:
Verb[edit]

iacuimus

  1. first-person plural perfect active indicative of iaceō
    1. "we have lain prostrate, we lay prostrate, we have lain down, we lay down; we have reclined, we reclined"
    2. "we have lain ill, we lay ill, we have been sick"
    3. "we have lingered, we lingered, we have tarried, we tarried"
    4. "we have been placed or situated, we have lain, we lay"
    5. "we have been low, flat or level"
    6. "we have lain still, we lay still"
    7. "we have lain dead, we lay dead"
    8. "we have lain in ruins, we lay in ruins"
    9. "we have hung down loose, we hung down loose"
    10. (of the face or eyes) "we have been fixed on the ground, we have been cast down"
    11. "we have been indolent, idle or inactive"
    12. "we have lain dormant or abandoned, we lay dormant or abandoned, we have been of no avail"
    13. "we have lain overthrown, we lay overthrown; we have been refuted; we have been despised"
    14. (of speech or language) "we have been languid, dull or lifeless"
